   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="original">
            <opener>
               <salute><persName key="#DR">Diego</persName>.</salute>
            </opener>
            <p> Verdad es, muy grande que yo no quisiera, ni hablar, ni dormir ni hoir, ni querer. </p>
            <p> Sentirme enamorada, sin miedo, a la sangre, sin tiempo ni magia, dentro de tu gran
               angustia, y, en el mismo ruido de tu corazon. Toda esta cura, si te la pidiera, yo sé
               que saria, para tu silencio, solo turbacion. </p>
            <p> Te pido violencia, en la sinrazon, y tu, me das gracia, tu luz y color. </p>
            <p> Pintarte quisiera, per no hay colores, por hablerlos tantos, en mi confusion, la
               forma concreta de mi gran amor. </p>
            <closer>
               <signed>
                  <choice>
                     <abbr><persName key="#FK">F.</persName></abbr>
                     <expan>Frida</expan>
                  </choice>
               </signed>
               <del>
                  <gap reason="cancelled" quantity="15" unit="character"/>
               </del>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
               <p> Cada momento, il es mi niño, mi niño nacido, cada talito, diario, de mi misma.
               </p>
            </postscript>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <opener>
               <salute><persName key="#DR">Diego</persName>.</salute>
            </opener>
            <p> Truth is, so great, that I wouldn’t like to speak, or sleep, or listen, or love. </p>
            <p> To feel myself trapped, with no fear of blood, outside time and magic, within your
               own fear, and your great anguish, and within the very beating of your heart. All this
               madness, if I asked it of you, I know, in your silence, there would be only
               confusion. </p>
            <p> I ask you for violence, in the nonsense, and you, you give me grace, your light and
               your warmth. </p>
            <p> I’d like to paint you, but there are no colors, because there are so many, in my
               confusion, the tangible form of my great love. </p>
            <closer>
               <signed>
                  <choice>
                     <abbr><persName key="#FK">F.</persName></abbr>
                     <expan>Frida</expan>
                  </choice>
               </signed>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
               <p> Every moment, he is my child, my born child, every little breath, daily, of
                  myself. </p>
            </postscript>
         </div>
